    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Let the youth be placed in the most favorable circumstances possible; for the company they keep, the principles they adopt, the habits they form, will settle the question of their usefulness here and of their future, eternal interests with a certainty that is infallible.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">3<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"5T 545.1\" data-link=\"113.2668\">Ibid., 5:545</span>.</span></a></sup>",
