    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "The dangers of the young are greatly increased as they are thrown into the society of a large number of their own age, of varied character and habits of life. Under these circumstances many parents are inclined to relax rather than redouble their own efforts to guard and control their children.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">6<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"CT 332.1\" data-link=\"23.1624\">Ibid., 332</span>.</span></a></sup>",
