    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Where Are the Evenings Spent?</strong>&mdash;Every son and daughter should be called to account if absent from home at night. Parents should know what company their children are in and at whose house they spend their evenings. Some children deceive their parents with falsehoods to avoid exposure of their wrong course.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">8<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"CT 332.1\" data-link=\"23.1624\">Counsels to Teachers, Parents, and Students, 332, 333</span>.</span></a></sup>",
