    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Guard your children from every objectionable influence possible; for in childhood they are more ready to receive impressions, either of moral dignity, purity, and loveliness of character, or of selfishness, impurity, and disobedience. Once let them become influenced by the <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"470\"></span> spirit of murmuring, pride, vanity, and impurity, and the taint may be as indelible as life itself.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">12<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"ST 4-16-1896\" data-link=\"820.13408\">The Signs of the Times, April 16, 1896</span>.</span></a></sup>",
